.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATETIME.SINCE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDateTime.since \- Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.since()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]since()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] instances returns a new
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object representing the duration from
another date\-time (in a form convertible by
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime.from()\f[R]) to this date\-time.
The duration is positive if the other date\-time is before this
date\-time, and negative if after.
.PP
This method does \f[CR]this \- other\f[R].
To do \f[CR]other \- this\f[R], use the \f[CR]until()\f[R] method.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
since(other)
since(other, options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]other\f[R]
A string, an object, or a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] instance
representing a date\-time to subtract from this date\-time.
It is converted to a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] object using the
same algorithm as \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime.from()\f[R].
It must have the same calendar as \f[CR]this\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An object containing the options for
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration.prototype.round()\f[R], which includes
\f[CR]largestUnit\f[R], \f[CR]roundingIncrement\f[R],
\f[CR]roundingMode\f[R], and \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R].
\f[CR]largestUnit\f[R] and \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R] accept all possible
units.
For \f[CR]largestUnit\f[R], the default value \f[CR]\(dqauto\(dq\f[R]
means \f[CR]\(dqdays\(dq\f[R] or \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R], whichever is
greater.
For \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R], the default value is
\f[CR]\(dqnanoseconds\(dq\f[R].
The current date is used as the \f[CR]relativeTo\f[R] option.
Note that using units larger than \f[CR]\(dqdays\(dq\f[R] may make the
duration not portable to other calendars or dates.
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object representing the duration
\f[I]since\f[R] \f[CR]other\f[R] to this date\-time.
The duration is positive if \f[CR]other\f[R] is before this date\-time,
and negative if after.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown in one of the following cases:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]other\f[R] has a different calendar than \f[CR]this\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
Any of the options is invalid.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using since()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] lastBilling = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from({
  year: Temporal.Now.plainDateISO().year,
  month: 4,
  day: 1,
});
\f[B]const\f[R] now = Temporal.Now.plainDateTimeISO().round(\(dqsecond\(dq);
\f[B]if\f[R] (Temporal.PlainDateTime.compare(lastBilling, now) > 0) {
  lastBilling = lastBilling.subtract({ years: 1 });
}
\f[B]const\f[R] duration = now.since(lastBilling);
console.log(\(ga${duration.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq)} since last billing\(ga);
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dq[number] days, [number] hr, [number] min, [number] sec since last billing\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] duration2 = now.since(lastBilling, { smallestUnit: \(dqdays\(dq });
console.log(\(ga${duration2.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq)} since last billing\(ga);
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dq[number] days since last billing\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] duration3 = now.since(lastBilling, {
  largestUnit: \(dqyears\(dq,
  smallestUnit: \(dqdays\(dq,
});
console.log(\(ga${duration3.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq)} since last billing\(ga);
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dq[number] months, [number] days since last billing\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SS Rounding the result
By default the fractional part of the \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R] is
truncated.
You can round it up using the \f[CR]roundingIncrement\f[R] and
\f[CR]roundingMode\f[R] options.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt1 = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from(\(dq2022\-01\-01T00:00:00\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] dt2 = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from(\(dq2022\-01\-28T12:34:56\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] duration = dt2.since(dt1, {
  smallestUnit: \(dqdays\(dq,
  roundingIncrement: 5,
  roundingMode: \(dqceil\(dq,
});
console.log(duration.toString()); \f[I]// \(dqP30D\(dq\f[R]
.EE
